description:
Simon Pooni was a young man with the world seemingly in the palm of his hand. A budding high school basketball star until his body was struck with the cruel disease multiple sclerosis. Confined to a wheelchair and losing sight in one eye, all of his friends desert him except for his teammate Chris.

One night after watching their favorite movie starring Tad Scott as the super hero Superior, a strange visitor enters Chris' life. A talking monkey in an astronaut suit named Ormon. Taking Chris to a distant dimension he transforms him into his hero, the mighty Superior. Discovering himself to be an exact replica of his hero with super strength, flight, invulnerability and super speed he sets out to help the world. Sharing his secret with his friend Chris this young man has become his hero Superior.

Collected in Superior.
name: Superior

deck: A series started in 1986 that was published originally by Crystal Comics then Apple Comics and created by Neil D. Vokes and Rich Rankin. It ran for 23 issues.
description:
Eagle was a comic series created by Neil D. Vokes and Rich Rankin following the vigilante Richard Eagle. Running a total of 23 issues before coming to an end in 1989, Eagle began it's run under Crystal Publications (Crystal Comics), a company started by Vokes and Rankin specifically so they could self-publish Eagle. However, when Crystal Publications closed up shop, Apple Comics picked up the series and published the last 7 issues.
Vokes and Rankin blend detective-style stories, martial arts, the occult, psychic powers and more to create this unique series.
name: Eagle
